%20has%20quashed%20the%20preventive%20detention%20of%20Kashmiri%20journalist%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EAasif%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0Sultan%20and%20directed%20the%20Union%20Territory%20administration%20to%20set%20him%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20delivering%20the%20judgement%2C%20a%20single%20bench%20of%20the%20High%20Court%20led%20by%20Justice%20V.%20C.%20Koul%20censured%20J%26amp%3BK%20authorities%20for%20refusing%20official%20documents%20to%20Sultan%20that%20could%20have%20enabled%20him%20to%20challenge%20his%20detention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ETerming%20his%20detention%20as%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20and%20unsustainable%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20court%20also%20reprimanded%20the%20authorities%20for%20not%20furnishing%20any%20credible%20evidence%20in%20court%2C%20as%20required%20under%20law%2C%20to%20prolong%20the%20detention%20of%20Sultan%20under%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20(PSA)%2C%20which%20has%20been%20termed%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Clawless%20law%E2%80%9D%20by%20Amnesty%20International.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20unambiguously%20clear%20and%20evident%20from%20perusal%20of%20receipt%20of%20grounds%20of%20detention%20and%20other%20relevant%20record%20that%20only%20five%20leaves%20have%20been%20given%20to%20detenu%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Koul%20observed%20in%20his%20judgement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20High%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20authorities%20in%20Kashmir%20didn%E2%80%99t%20provide%20Sultan%20with%20the%20copies%20of%20the%20FIR%2C%20witness%20statements%20or%20other%20investigation%20material%20of%20the%20case%20which%20formed%20the%20basis%20for%20his%20preventive%20detention%20under%20the%20PSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Koul%20asked%20the%20authorities%20to%20set%20Sultan%20free%20%E2%80%9Cforthwith%20provided%20he%20is%20not%20required%20in%20any%20other%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20controversial%20dossier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20PSA%20dossier%2C%20authorities%20in%20Kashmir%20had%20accused%20the%20award-winning%20journalist%20of%20being%20an%20%E2%80%9Cover-ground%20worker%20of%20Hizbul%20Mujahideen%E2%80%9D%20who%20curiously%20joined%20Al-Qaida%20affiliate%2C%20Ansar%20Ghazwat-ul-Hind%2C%20while%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dossier%20also%20claimed%20that%20Sultan%20was%20working%20as%20an%20over-ground%20worker%20of%20The%20Resistance%20Front%2C%20a%20militant%20group%20which%20was%20set%20up%20months%20after%20Sultan%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20in%202018%20and%20which%20authorities%20believe%20is%20an%20offshoot%20of%20Pakistan%20Lashkar-e-Toiba%20terror%20outfit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20comes%20more%20than%20five%20years%20after%20Sultan%2C%20who%20was%20working%20with%20the%20now%20defunct%2C%20monthly%20English%20magazine%20%3Cem%3EKashmir%20Narrator%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20accused%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20of%20harbouring%20terrorists%20at%20his%20Srinagar%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESultan%20was%20later%20booked%20under%20the%20provisions%20of%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20and%20Ranbir%20Penal%20Code%20(now%20Indian%20Penal%20Code)%20in%202018%20and%20arrested%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20which%20claimed%20to%20have%20recovered%20%E2%80%9Cincriminating%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20from%20his%20residence%20during%20searches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20court%20in%20Srinagar%20granted%20him%20bail%20in%20the%20case%20on%20April%205%20last%20year%2C%20citing%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20investigators%20in%20providing%20evidence%20that%20linked%20him%20to%20any%20militant%20group%20while%20ordering%20his%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20authorities%20invoked%20PSA%20against%20Sultan%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20%E2%80%9Charnessing%20known%20militants%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccriminal%20conspiracy%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Caiding%20and%20participating%20in%20militant%20activities%E2%80%9D.%20He%20was%20taken%20into%20preventive%20detention%20under%20PSA%20and%20later%20shifted%20to%20Agra%20Central%20Jail%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Public%20Safety%20Act%2C%20which%20was%20introduced%20in%201978%20to%20curb%20the%20menace%20of%20timber%20smuggling%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20allows%20for%20suspects%20to%20be%20held%20for%20up%20to%20two%20years%20in%20preventive%20detention%20without%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20resident%20of%20Srinagar%E2%80%99s%20Batamaloo%2C%20Sultan%20was%20awarded%20the%20annual%C2%A0John%20Aubuchon%20Press%20Freedom%20Award%C2%A0by%20the%20National%20Press%20Club%20of%20America%20on%20October%2017%2C%202019.%20Sultan%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20was%20six-months%20old%20when%20he%20was%20arrested%20by%20police.%20He%20completed%20five%20years%20in%20incarceration%20on%20August%2027%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20among%20other%20press%20freedom%20advocacy%20groups%20across%20the%20world%20have%20been%20urging%20India%20to%20release%20Sultan%20%E2%80%9Cunconditionally%E2%80%9D%20while%20accusing%20authorities%20of%20%E2%80%9Cweaponizing%20preventative%20detention%20and%20anti-terror%20laws%20against%20journalists%20to%20muzzle%20their%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20long%20arm%20of%20the%20PSA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20nearly%20400%20journalists%20and%20civil%20society%20members%20had%20called%20on%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20release%20Sultan.%20In%20February%202022%2C%2057%20press%20freedom%20organisations%2C%20rights%20groups%2C%20and%20publications%20had%20urged%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20to%20release%20all%20arbitrarily%20detained%20journalists%2C%20including%20Sultan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20on%20Sultan%20comes%20days%20after%20the%20high%20court%20delivered%20two%20similar%20and%20consecutive%20judgements%20ordering%20the%20authorities%20to%20free%20Kashmiri%20journalists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fafter-nearly-2-years-jk-hc-grants-bail-to-kashmir-walla-editor-fahad-shah%5C%22%3EFahad%20Shah%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjk-high-court-quashes-psa-proceedings-against-sajad-gul-rebukes-admin-for-not-applying-its-mind%5C%22%3ESajad%20Gul%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20were%20also%20taken%20into%20preventive%20detention%20under%20PSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20have%20launched%20multiple%20terror%20investigations%20against%20Shah%2C%20the%20editor%20of%20Srinagar-based%20digital%20news%20outlet%20%E2%80%98The%20Kashmir%20Walla%E2%80%99%2C%20Gul%20was%20booked%20under%20criminal%20conspiracy%20and%20other%20charges.%20However%2C%20barring%20one%20case%20against%20Gul%2C%20the%20courts%20granted%20bail%20to%20both%20the%20journalists%20in%20these%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Mohammad%20Manan%20Dar%2C%20a%20Srinagar-based%20photojournalist%2C%20who%20was%20arrested%20in%20a%20terror%20conspiracy%20case%20by%20the%20National%20Investigations%20Agency%2C%20was%20released%20on%20bail%20by%20a%20court%20which%20termed%20the%20charges%20against%20him%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmere%20assumptions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20press%20freedom%20in%20India%20has%20suffered%20relentless%20blows.%20In%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20the%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20Index%20placed%20India%20at%20161%20out%20of%20180%20countries%20this%20year%2C%2011%20spots%20further%20down%20from%20the%202022%20ranking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%2C%20India%20has%20been%20using%20%E2%80%9Ccharges%20of%20defamation%2C%20sedition%2C%20contempt%20of%20court%20and%20endangering%20national%20security%20%E2%80%A6%20increasingly%20..%20against%20journalists%20critical%20of%20the%20government%2C%20who%20are%20branded%20as%20%E2%80%98anti-national%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20denied%20these%20charges%20while%20accusing%20the%20Paris-based%20press%20freedom%20watchdog%20of%20%E2%80%9Csubverting%20the%20democratic%20freedoms%20all%20over%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702357185000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12101710%2FUntitled-design-16-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Faasif-sultan-kashmir-journalist-detention-free%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20also%20reprimanded%20the%20authorities%20for%20not%20furnishing%20any%20credible%20evidence%20in%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Faasif-sultan-kashmir-journalist-detention-free%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Another%20Surprise%20Awaits%3F%20BJP%20May%20Announce%20Rajasthan%20Chief%20Minister%20Today%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHaving%20sprung%20two%20surprises%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20BJP%20is%20likely%20to%20announce%20the%20name%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%20for%20Rajasthan%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP's%20newly%20elected%20MLAs%20are%20scheduled%20to%20meet%20in%20Jaipur%20at%204%20pm%20to%20pick%20the%20legislative%20party%20leader%2C%20and%20all%20eyes%20will%20be%20on%20whether%20the%20party%20decides%20to%20go%20with%20its%20best-known%20face%20in%20the%20state%2C%20two-time%20chief%20minister%20Vasundhara%20Raje%2C%20or%20effect%20a%20generational%20change%2C%20like%20it%20has%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20State%20General%20Secretary%20and%20MLA%20Bhajanlal%20Sharma%20said%20the%20meeting%20will%20take%20place%20at%20the%20party%20headquarters%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20BJP's%20central%20observer%20and%20Union%20Defence%20Minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%2C%20and%20two%20co-observers%2C%20National%20General%20Secretary%20Vinod%20Tawde%20and%20National%20Vice%20President%20Saroj%20Pandey.%20All%20party%20MLAs%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20attend%20the%20meeting%2C%20where%20the%20name%20of%20the%20new%20chief%20minister%20will%20be%20announced%2C%20Mr%20Sharma%20told%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20won%20115%20seats%20in%20the%20200-member%20Assembly%20in%20the%20elections%2C%20whose%20results%20were%20declared%20on%20December%203.%20Polling%20did%20not%20take%20place%20in%20the%20Karanpur%20seat%20of%20Sriganganagar%20district%20after%20the%20death%20of%20Congress%20candidate%20Gurmeet%20Singh%20Kooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20elections%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20not%20declared%20Ms%20Raje%20the%20chief%20ministerial%20face%20and%20had%20decided%20to%20bank%20on%20collective%20leadership%20and%20the%20popularity%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20unseat%20the%20Ashok%20Gehlot-led%20Congress%20government%2C%20which%20was%20seen%20as%20having%20a%20strong%20chance%20of%20bucking%20the%20state's%20revolving-door%20policy%20because%20of%20the%20popularity%20of%20its%20welfare%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Raje%20is%20still%20seen%20as%20a%20frontrunner%20for%20the%20post%2C%20along%20with%20Union%20ministers%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%2C%20Gajendra%20Singh%20Shekhawat%20and%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw.%20The%20other%20contenders%20are%20Diya%20Kumari%20from%20the%20erstwhile%20Jaipur%20royal%20family%2C%20state%20unit%20chief%20CP%20Joshi%20and%20senior%20leader%20Kirodi%20Lal%20Meena.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20speculation%20that%20the%20party%2C%20which%20has%20chosen%20an%20OBC%20leader%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20a%20tribal%20leader%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20could%20pick%20a%20woman%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20is%20being%20seen%20as%20a%20show%20of%20support%2C%20several%20newly%20elected%20MLAs%20have%20been%20meeting%20Ms%20Raje%20ahead%20of%20the%20legislative%20party%20meet.%20Nearly%2010%20MLAs%20had%20gone%20to%20her%20residence%20on%20Sund