is%20means%20that%20out%20of%20697%20players%20whose%20social%20media%20accounts%20were%20monitored%2C%20152%20were%20targeted%20with%20discriminatory%2C%20abusive%2C%20or%20threatening%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlarmingly%2C%20players%20at%20the%20Women's%20World%20Cup%20were%2029%25%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20online%20abuse%20than%20those%20at%20the%20men's%20tournament%20in%20Qatar.%20To%20combat%20this%20issue%2C%20FIFA%20implemented%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fifa.com%2Fsocial-impact%2Fcampaigns%2Fno-discrimination%2Fmedia-releases%2Ffifa-and-fifpro-release-report-on-the-social-media-protection-service-at-the%5C%22%3ESocial%20Media%20Protection%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%20(SMPS)%2C%20which%20allows%20players%20to%20opt-in%20for%20moderation%20services%20that%20can%20hide%20abusive%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20were%20derived%20from%20the%20examination%20of%20data%20generated%20by%20FIFA's%20Social%20Media%20Protection%20Service%20(SMPS).%20The%20SMPS%20employed%20artificial%20intelligence%20software%20to%20scrutinize%20millions%20of%20posts%20for%20abusive%20content.%20The%20AI%20tool%20responsible%20for%20this%20analysis%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BThreat%20Matrix%2C%26quot%3B%20introduced%20as%20a%20component%20of%20FIFA's%20social%20media%20protection%20service%20the%20previous%20year.%20The%20Threat%20Matrix%20actively%20monitors%20user%20activity%20across%20prominent%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20such%20as%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20Instagram%2C%20Facebook%2C%20TikTok%2C%20and%20YouTube.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SMPS%20data%20showed%20that%20the%20United%20States%20women's%20team%20-%20which%20has%20routinely%20been%20targeted%20for%20online%20abuse%20over%20the%20years%20-%20was%20subjected%20to%20most%20abuse%20during%20the%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFIFA%20said%20two%20players%20-%20one%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20one%20from%20Argentina%2C%20whose%20identities%20were%20not%20revealed%20-%20were%20targeted%20above%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColombian%20player%20Leicy%20Santos%20was%20quoted%20in%20the%20report%20saying%20the%20abuse%20was%20harmful%20to%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there%20is%20one%20thing%20that%20footballers%20suffer%20from%20the%20most%2C%20apart%20from%20losing%2C%20it%20is%20all%20the%20abusive%20comments%20-%20the%20taunts%2C%20the%20insults%2C%26quot%3B%20Santos%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeyond%20what%20we%20do%20as%20professional%20footballers%2C%20we%20are%20people.%20Some%20players%20are%20able%20to%20put%20up%20with%20the%20outrageous%20abuse%20we%20receive%20online%2C%20but%20other%20players%20aren't.%20It%20is%20a%20very%20sensitive%20issue%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20mental%20health.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFIFA%20President%20Gianni%20Infantino%20meanwhile%20vowed%20no%20let%20up%20in%20the%20battle%20to%20tackle%20player%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20can%20be%20no%20place%20on%20social%20media%20for%20those%20who%20abuse%20or%20threaten%20anyone%2C%20be%20that%20in%20FIFA%20tournaments%20or%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInfantino%20said%20that%20since%20the%20SMPS%20system%20was%20first%20introduced%20last%20year%2C%20players%2C%20teams%20and%20officials%20had%20been%20shielded%20from%20more%20than%20400%2C000%20abusive%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDiscrimination%20has%20no%20place%20in%20football%20and%20no%20place%20in%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Infantino%20added.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(With%20inputs%20from%20AFP)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702352760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F0g5jr1vg_2023-fifa-womens-world-cup_625x300_12_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2F2023-fifa-womens-world-cup-one-in-five-womens-world-cup-players-targeted-with-online-abuse-fifa-report-finds-4657727%