%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22COP28%3A%20Just%20A%20Day%20Left%2C%20Yet%20Latest%20Draft%20of%20Global%20Stocktake%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Inspire%20Hope%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12084953%2FGBDJQ7nWEAAE0mJ.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%E2%80%99s%20less%20than%20a%20day%20left%20of%20COP28.%20But%20not%20enough%20ground%20has%20been%20covered%20in%20many%20aspects%3B%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20current%20COP%20could%20be%20regression%20when%20compared%20to%20advances%20made%20at%20previous%20COPs%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReleased%20by%20the%20COP28%20presidency%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20December%2011%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresource%2FGST_2.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elatest%20draft%20text%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20much-awaited%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%20%E2%80%93%20the%20final%20draft%20of%20which%20is%20meant%20to%20help%20countries%20redraw%20their%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%20(a%20set%20of%20voluntary%20steps%20each%20nation%20proposes%20to%20take%2C%20to%20tackle%20and%20curb%20climate%20change)%20by%202025%20%E2%80%93%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointing%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cweak%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20mess%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwatered%20down%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20no%20mention%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20phase%20outs%2C%20experts%20said.%20They%20added%20that%20the%20draft%20keeps%20the%20world%20out%20of%20reach%20of%20the%201.5%C2%B0%20Celsius%20target.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20first%20draft%20text%20on%20the%20Global%20Goal%20on%20Adaptation%20%E2%80%93%20activities%20that%20encompass%20ways%20in%20which%20people%20and%20communities%20can%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20also%20leaves%20much%20to%20be%20desired%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20delivering%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20statement%20on%20December%209%20at%20Dubai%2C%20UAE%2C%20where%20the%20COP%20is%20ongoing%2C%20union%20environment%20minister%20Bhupender%20Yadav%20highlighted%20the%20importance%20of%20equity%20and%20climate%20justice%20in%20global%20climate%20action%2C%20and%20said%20that%20this%20can%20be%20ensured%20only%20when%20developed%20countries%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20the%20lead%20in%20ambitious%20climate%20action%E2%80%9D.%20He%20had%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20clear%20definition%20of%20climate%20finance%20is%20also%20crucial%20given%20its%20importance%20for%20least%20developed%20and%20developing%20countries%2C%20and%20ones%20that%20are%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20climate%20change.%20The%20latest%20draft%20of%20the%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%20does%20not%20define%20climate%20finance%20either%2C%20experts%20pointed%20out.%20A%20final%20draft%20of%20the%20GST%20is%20expected%20early%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%2012%20year-old%20Licypriya%20Kangujam%2C%20a%20child%20climate%20activist%20from%20India%2C%20protested%20on%20the%20stage%20at%20the%20UN%20High%20Level%20Plenary%20Session%20on%20December%2011%20at%20COP28%2C%20asking%20that%20fossil%20fuels%20be%20phased%20out%20for%20a%20safe%20future%20for%20children.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EHere%20is%20the%20full%20video%20of%20my%20protest%20today%20disrupting%20the%20UN%20High%20Level%20Plenary%20Session%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FCOP28UAE%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23COP28UAE%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20detained%20me%20for%20over%2030%20minutes%20after%20this%20protest.%20My%20only%20crime-%20Asking%20to%20Phase%20Out%20Fossil%20Fuels%2C%20the%20top%20cause%20of%20climate%20crisis%20today.%20Now%20they%20kicked%20me%20out%20of%20COP28.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FToPIJ3K9zM%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FToPIJ3K9zM%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Licypriya%20Kangujam%20(%40LicypriyaK)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLicypriyaK%2Fstatus%2F1734235118175420874%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2011%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELatest%20draft%20of%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Global%20Stocktake%20(GST)%20is%2C%20per%20the%20UN%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20process%20for%20countries%20and%20stakeholders%20to%20see%20where%20they%E2%80%99re%20collectively%20making%20progress%20towards%20meeting%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20Agreement%20%E2%80%93%20and%20where%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%E2%80%9D.%20The%20GST%20will%20inform%20the%20next%20round%20of%20climate%20action%20plans%20under%20the%202015%20Paris%20Agreement%20(helping%20countries%20reframe%20their%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%2C%20or%20NDCs%2C%20which%20are%20voluntary%20steps%20each%20nation%20proposes%20to%20take%20to%20tackle%20and%20curb%20climate%20change)%20to%20be%20put%20forward%20by%202025.%20The%20GST%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most-awaited%20outcomes%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20COP%20because%20it%20is%20hosting%20the%20first%20round%20of%20the%20GST.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20previous%20draft%20of%20the%20GST%20that%20the%20COP28%20presidency%20released%20retained%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20phase-out%20option%20but%20did%20not%20incorporate%20the%20proposal%20by%20developing%20countries%20to%20add%20the%20terms%20%E2%80%98just%20and%20equitable%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98developed%20countries%20taking%20the%20lead%E2%80%99.%20%E2%80%9CWithout%20equity%2C%20it%20is%20neither%20fair%20nor%20feasible%20to%20accelerate%20the%20green%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20developing%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20Harjeet%20Singh%2C%20Head%20%E2%80%93%20Global%20Political%20Strategy%2C%20Climate%20Action%20Network%20International%2C%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fharjeet11%2Fstatus%2F1733138154725540316%3Fs%3D46%26t%3DvqtpLTbqF8SPMCvqYAO_5g%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecommented%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20about%20this%20version.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UNFCCC%20uploaded%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresource%2FGST_2.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elatest%20draft%20text%20of%20the%20document%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20prepared%20by%20the%20COP28%20president%2C%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20December%2011%2C%20the%20penultimate%20day%20of%20the%20UN%20climate%20conference.%20As%20per%20the%20new%20document%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9Crecognizes%20the%20need%20for%20deep%2C%20rapid%20and%20sustained%20reductions%20in%20GHG%20emissions%20and%20calls%20upon%20Parties%20to%20take%20actions%20that%20could%20include%2C%20inter%20alia%E2%80%9D%2C%20activities%20such%20as%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20globally%20and%20doubling%20the%20global%20average%20annual%20rate%20of%20energy%20efficiency%20improvements%20by%202030%2C%20accelerating%20global%20efforts%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20emissions%20from%20energy%20systems%2C%20and%20utilizing%20zero%20and%20low%20carbon%20fuels%20well%20before%20or%20by%20around%20mid-century%2C%20and%20reducing%20emissions%20from%20road%20transport%20through%20means%20such%20as%20developing%20infrastructure%20and%20rapid%20deployment%20of%20zero%20and%20low%20emission%20vehicles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-first-day-agreement-loss-and-damage-deal-fund%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3EFirst%20Day%20of%20COP28%20Talks%3A%20Agreement%20on%20Loss%20and%20Damage%20Deal%20Reached%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20text%20pushes%20forward%20the%20concept%20of%20carbon%20capture%20utilisation%20and%20storage%20(CCUS)%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAccelerating%20zero%20and%20low%20emissions%20technologies%2C%20including%2C%20inter%20alia%2C%20renewables%2C%20nuclear%2C%20abatement%20and%20removal%20technologies%2C%20including%20such%20as%20carbon%20capture%20and%20utilization%20and%20storage%2C%20and%20low%20carbon%20hydrogen%20production%2C%20so%20as%20to%20enhance%20efforts%20towards%20substitution%20of%20unabated%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20energy%20systems.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20CCUS%20is%20a%20highly%20controversial%20technique%20for%20carbon%20removal.%20It%20aims%20to%20store%20emissions%20from%20large%20polluting%20sources%20by%20means%20such%20as%20injecting%20them%20into%20deep%20geological%20formations%20%E2%80%93%20and%20scientists%20say%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20yet%20that%20CCUS%20will%20help%20reduce%20the%20impact%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20on%20global%20warming.%20Abated%20fossil%20fuels%20are%20those%20where%20CCUS%20technologies%20are%20used%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccapture%E2%80%9D%20most%20of%20the%20emissions%20released.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20unabated%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20the%20emissions%20are%20released%20directly%20into%20the%20air.%20Abated%20and%20unabated%20fossil%20fuels%20have%20been%20a%20major%20talking%20point%20at%20COP28.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20%E2%80%9Cphase%20out%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20draft%20GST%20text%20talks%20about%20is%20that%20of%20phasing%20out%20inefficient%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPhasing%20out%20of%20inefficient%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20that%20encourage%20wasteful%20consumption%20and%20do%20not%20address%20energy%20poverty%20or%20just%20transitions%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20draft%20text%20reads.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20the%20only%20%E2%80%9Cphase%20down%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20draft%20text%20talks%20about%20is%20that%20of%20rapidly%20phasing%20down%20%E2%80%9Cunabated%20coal%E2%80%9D%20and%20limiting%20permits%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20and%20unabated%20coal%20power%20generation%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20talks%20only%20about%20%E2%80%9Creducing%E2%80%9D%20both%20the%20consumption%20and%20production%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjust%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%20manner%20so%20as%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20by%2C%20before%2C%20or%20around%202050%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20GST%20text%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20represents%20%E2%80%9Ca%20significant%20regression%20from%20previous%20versions%E2%80%9D%2C%20commented%20Harjeet%20Singh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAstonishingly%2C%20it%20has%20dropped%20explicit%20language%20on%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20opting%20instead%20for%20a%20vague%20commitment%20to%20%E2%80%98reduce%20both%20consumption%20and%20production%E2%80%99%20by%202050.%20This%20is%20a%20clear%20indication%20of%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20industry%E2%80%99s%20lobbying%20power%2C%20influencing%20global%20policies%20to%20favour%20prolonged%20fossil%20fuel%20use%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20fail%20to%20issue%20a%20decisive%20and%20strong%20directive%20from%20COP28%2C%20we%20stand%20at%20the%20precipice%20of%20crossing%20the%20crucial%201.5%C2%B0%20Celsius%20warming%20threshold.%20Such%20a%20scenario%20would%20unleash%20catastrophic%20consequences%20globally%2C%20disproportionately%20affecting%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20communities%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Disappointing%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98weak%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98watered%20down%E2%80%99%3A%20More%20experts%20weigh%20in%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20new%20GST%20text%20fundamentally%20puts%201.5%C2%B0C%20out%20of%20reach%2C%E2%80%9D%20Climate%20Analytics%20CEO%20Bill%20Hare%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20Germany-based%20Climate%20Analytics%20is%20a%20global%20science%20and%20policy%20institute%20delivering%20cutting-edge%20science%2C%20analysis%20and%20support%20to%20accelerate%20climate%20action%20and%20keep%20warming%20below%201.5%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20energy%20package%20is%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20weak%E2%80%9D%20and%20includes%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20include%2C%20inter%20alia%E2%80%9D%20which%20means%20that%20everything%20is%20optional%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20Latin%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Cinter%20alia%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20means%20%E2%80%9Camong%20other%20things%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20mention%20of%20deadlines%20have%20been%20watered%20down%20along%20with%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98phase%20out%E2%80%99.%20The%20coal%20language%20is%20actually%20a%20step%20backwards%20from%20the%20text%20in%20the%20Glasgow%20Climate%20Pact.%20The%20reference%20to%20production%20and%20consumption%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20is%20completely%20open%20in%20terms%20of%20timeframe%20and%20allows%20this%20to%20be%20done%20essentially%20with%20offsets%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20use%20of%20%E2%80%98unabated%E2%80%99%20clearly%20allows%20new%20fossil%20infrastructure%20to%20be%20built%2C%20against%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20IEA%20and%20others.%20There%20also%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20cherry%20picking%20of%20technologies%20like%20CCUS%20and%20low%20carbon%20hydrogen%20%E2%80%93%20opening%20the%20way%20for%20blue%20hydrogen%20made%20with%20natural%20gas%E2%80%A6Critically%20there%20is%20also%20nothing%20on%20how%20the%20GST%20will%20act%20to%20close%20the%202030%20emissions%20gap.%20This%20text%20is%20a%20mess%20and%20it%20is%20pushing%20false%20solutions%2C%20endangering%20us%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fphase-out-fossil-fuels-46-million-healthcare-professionals-cop28-presidency%5C%22%3EPhase%20Out%20Fossil%20Fuels%20for%20Healthy%20World%3A%2046%20Million%20Healthcare%20Professionals%20Write%20to%20COP28%20Presidency%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimateanalytics.org%2Fpublications%2Funabated-the-carbon-capture-and-storage-86-billion-tonne-carbon-bomb-aimed-at-derailing-a-fossil-phase-out%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20released%20by%20Climate%20Analytics%20on%20December%205%2C%20reliance%20on%20carbon%20capture%20and%20storage%20could%20release%20an%20extra%2086%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20between%202020%20and%202050.%20Per%20the%20analysis%2C%20opening%20up%20%E2%80%98abated%E2%80%99%20fossil%20fuels%20could%20push%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%E2%80%99s%201.5%C2%B0C%20warming%20limit%20out%20of%20reach%20%E2%80%94%20given%20the%20expansion%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20projects%20being%20currently%20promoted%20around%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20term%20%E2%80%98abated%E2%80%99%20is%20being%20used%20as%20a%20trojan%20horse%20to%20allow%20fossil%20fuels%20with%20dismal%20capture%20rates%20to%20count%20as%20climate%20action.%20%E2%80%98Abated%E2%80%99%20may%20sound%20like%20harmless%20jargon%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20actually%20language%20deliberately%20engineered%20and%20heavily%20promoted%20by%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20to%20create%20the%20illusion%20we%20can%20keep%20expanding%20fossil%20fuels%2C%E2%80%9D%20report%20author%20Claire%20Fyson%20of%20Climate%20Analytics%20had%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAl%20Gore%2C%20former%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%20said%20that%20COP28%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnow%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20failure%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ECOP28%20is%20now%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20complete%20failure.%20The%20world%20desperately%20needs%20to%20phase%20out%20fossil%20fuels%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%20but%20this%20obsequious%20draft%20reads%20as%20if%20OPEC%20dictated%20it%20word%20for%20word.%20It%20is%20even%20worse%20than%20many%20had%20feared.%20It%20is%20%E2%80%9COf%20the%20Petrostates%2C%20By%20the%20Petrostates%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Al%20Gore%20(%40algore)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Falgore%2Fstatus%2F1734238192608411989%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2011%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cb%3EVagueness%20is%20an%20issue%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20GST%20text%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointing%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20be%20ineffective%20in%20curbing%20global%20warming%E2%80%9D%2C%20commented%20Siddharth%20Goel%2C%20Senior%20Policy%20Advisor%2C%20International%20Institute%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20(IISD).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20uses%20vague%20phrasing%20like%20%E2%80%98could%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%98must%E2%80%99%20in%20urging%20countries%20to%20meet%20key%20climate%20targets%2C%20despite%20past%20experience%20clearly%20demonstrating%20that%20several%20countries%20have%20not%20upheld%20even%20voluntary%20commitments.%20It%20also%20opens%20the%20door%20to%20fossil-dependent%20technologies%2C%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98low-carbon%20hydrogen%20production%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20continues%20to%20include%20vague%20language%2C%20such%20as%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98inefficient%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%E2%80%99%2C%C2%A0%20which%20has%20created%20significant%20ambiguity%20about%20what%20policies%20should%20be%20reformed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20also%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20large%20emerging%20economies%20like%20India%2C%20by%20refusing%20to%20scale%20up%20and%20hold%20developed%20countries%20to%20account%20in%20meeting%20their%20finance%20commitments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20GST%20text%20also%20notes%20the%20complexity%20arising%20from%20the%20diversity%20of%20definitions%20of%20climate%20finance%20used%20by%20party%20and%20non-party%20stakeholders%20in%20the%20context%20of%20aggregate%20accounting%20and%20reporting%20of%20climate%20finance%2C%20commented%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EVaibhav%20Chaturvedi%2C%20Fellow%2C%20Council%20on%20Energy%2C%20Environment%20and%20Water%20(CEEW)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20environment%20minister%20had%20highlighted%20the%20same%20concern%20recently%20during%20the%20negotiations.%20Lack%20of%20definition%20is%20a%20great%20escape%20for%20the%20developed%20world.%20It%20is%20an%20elegant%20strategy%20%E2%80%93%20don%E2%80%99t%20define%20it%20so%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20measure%20and%20monitor%20climate%20finance%20commitments%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EChaturvedi%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20say%20you%20recognise%20and%20respect%20the%20science%20but%20then%20fail%20to%20take%20heed%20of%20its%20dire%20warnings%20in%20the%20collective%20action%20you%20commit%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20commented%20former%20Ireland%20president%20Mary%20Robinson%2C%20currently%20chair%20of%20The%20Elders%2C%20an%20independent%20group%20of%20global%20leaders%20working%20for%20peace%2C%20justice%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20a%20sustainable%20planet%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20by%20Nelson%20Mandela%20in%202007.%20Robinson%20was%20directly%20referencing%20the%20text%20of%20the%20draft%20GST%20in%20her%20comments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20note%20with%20%E2%80%9Calarm%20and%20serious%20concern%E2%80%9D%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20IPCC%20Sixth%20Assessment%20Report%20and%20the%20damage%20being%20caused%20already%20by%20climate%20change%20but%20then%20fail%20to%20put%20in%20place%20the%20steps%20the%20science%20recommends%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20say%20you%20reaffirm%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20but%20to%20then%20fail%20to%20commit%20to%20a%20full%20fossil%20fuel%20phase%20out.%20It%20is%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20use%20weak%20language%20or%20to%20permit%20loopholes%20for%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20industry%20to%20continue%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20very%20problem%20countries%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20committed%20to%20tackling%20here%20in%20Dubai.%20Adequate%20time%20and%20opportunity%20still%20lie%20ahead%2C%20provided%20that%20nations%20promptly%20return%20to%20the%20negotiating%20table%2C%20equipped%20with%20the%20resolve%20required%20for%20a%20crisis%20of%20this%20magnitude%20and%20a%20readiness%20to%20undertake%20the%20necessary%20measures.%20This%20current%20version%20of%20the%20COP28%20text%20is%20grossly%20insufficient.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20text%20is%20insufficient%20%26amp%3B%20unacceptable.%20It%20recognizes%20science%20but%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20act%20on%20it%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20%26amp%3B%20urgent%20action%20to%202030.%20It%20falls%20way%20short%20of%20what%20the%20world%20needs.%20Now%20we%20need%20courageous%20course%20correction%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fclimatemorgan%2Fstatus%2F1734285698163773769%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Jennifer%20Morgan%2C%20State%20Secretary%20and%20Special%20Envoy%20for%20International%20Climate%20Action%2C%20Federal%20Foreign%20Office%20of%20Germany.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3