ce%20left%20the%20state%20because%20she%20cannot%20wait%20any%20longer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Texas%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20against%20Kate%20Cox%2C%20a%20woman%20who%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20in%20Texas%20after%20being%20denied%20an%20abortion.%20The%20ruling%2C%20on%20Monday%20evening%2C%20came%20three%20days%20after%20the%20court%20temporarily%20halted%20a%20lower%20judge's%20ruling%20that%20gave%20Cox%20permission%20to%20get%20an%20abortion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECox%2C%20whose%20fetus%20has%20a%20fatal%20condition%2C%20left%20the%20state%20to%20get%20an%20abortion%20elsewhere%20before%20the%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%20rejected%20her%20unprecedented%20challenge%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20restrictive%20bans%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2031-year-old%20mother%20of%20two%20had%20spent%20nearly%20a%20week%20seeking%20court%20permission%20in%20Texas%20to%20end%20her%20pregnancy%2C%20but%20her%20attorney%20said%20she%20could%20not%20wait%20any%20longer%20and%20left%20the%20state.%20Her%20baby%20has%20a%20condition%20known%20as%20trisomy%2018%2C%20which%20has%20low%20survival%20rates%2C%20and%20her%20lawsuit%20argued%20that%20continuing%20the%20pregnancy%20jeopardized%20both%20her%20health%20and%20ability%20to%20have%20more%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas'%20abortion%20ban%20makes%20narrow%20exceptions%20when%20the%20life%20of%20the%20mother%20is%20in%20danger%20but%20not%20for%20fetal%20anomalies.%20Republican%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fken-paxton-halting-abortion-pregnant-woman-fetal-anomaly-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAttorney%20General%20Ken%20Paxton%3C%2Fa%3E%20argued%20that%20Cox%20had%20not%20shown%20that%20any%20of%20the%20complications%20in%20her%20pregnancy%20rose%20to%20the%20level%20of%20threatening%20her%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHer%20health%20is%20on%20the%20line.%20She's%20been%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20emergency%20room%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fabortion-care-wait-times-us-roe-dobbs-7b0a328bb34b0acb3d37e359a63712fc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe%20couldn't%20wait%20any%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20Nancy%20Northup%2C%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Reproductive%20Rights%2C%20which%20was%20representing%20Cox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20organization%20did%20not%20disclose%20where%20Cox%20went.%20On%20Monday%2C%20she%20would%20have%20been%2020%20weeks%20and%20six%20days%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHours%20after%20Cox's%20attorneys%20announced%20she%20had%20left%20Texas%2C%20the%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20issued%20its%20decision%20that%20ruled%20against%20Cox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20disputes%20that%20Ms.%20Cox's%20pregnancy%20has%20been%20extremely%20complicated.%20Any%20parents%20would%20be%20devastated%20to%20learn%20of%20their%20unborn%20child's%20trisomy%2018%20diagnosis%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSome%20difficulties%20in%20pregnancy%2C%20however%2C%20even%20serious%20ones%2C%20do%20not%20pose%20the%20heightened%20risks%20to%20the%20mother%20the%20exception%20encompasses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECox%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20Dallas%20area%2C%20was%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20first%20pregnant%20person%20in%20the%20US%20to%20ask%20a%20court%20for%20permission%20for%20an%20abortion%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fabortion-dobbs-anniversary-state-laws-51c2a83899f133556e715342abfcface%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoe%20v.%20Wade%20was%20overturned%20last%20year.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Her%20lawsuit%20quickly%20became%20a%20high-profile%20test%20of%20bans%20in%20Texas%20and%20a%20dozen%20other%20GOP-controlled%20states%2C%20where%20abortion%20is%20prohibited%20at%20nearly%20all%20stages%20of%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDays%20after%20Cox%20filed%20her%20lawsuit%2C%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20in%20Kentucky%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fabortion-kentucky-aclu-lawsuit-14df6d5e8a5aaa36009557d080b1c779%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%20a%20court%20to%20allow%20an%20abortion.%3C%2Fa%3E%20There%20has%20been%20no%20ruling%20yet%20in%20that%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Texas%2C%20Paxton%20mounted%20an%20aggressive%20defense%20to%20try%20to%20prevent%20Cox%20from%20having%20an%20abortion.%20He%20sent%20three%20Houston%20hospitals%20letters%20warning%20of%20legal%20consequences%20%E2%80%94%20both%20criminal%20and%20civil%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20allowed%20Cox's%20physician%20to%20provide%20the%20procedure.%20He%20also%20argued%20that%20Cox%20had%20not%20demonstrated%20that%20her%20life%20was%20at%20imminent%20risk%2C%20including%20noting%20that%20she%20was%20sent%20home%20after%20her%20multiple%20visits%20to%20emergency%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECox%20had%20cesarean%20surgeries%20during%20her%20first%20two%20pregnancies.%20Her%20lawsuit%20argued%20that%20inducing%20labor%20would%20carry%20a%20risk%20of%20a%20uterine%20rupture%20because%20of%20her%20prior%20C-sections%2C%20and%20that%20another%20one%20at%20full%20term%20would%20endanger%20her%20ability%20to%20carry%20another%20child.%20But%20Paxton%20contended%20those%20arguments%20still%20fell%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRather%2C%20the%20only%20question%20is%20whether%20Ms.%20Cox's%20condition%20meets%20the%20exception%2C%20regardless%20of%20how%20long%20the%20child%20is%20expected%20to%20live%2C%26quot%3B%20Paxton's%20office%20told%20the%20court%20in%20a%20filing%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Leilah%20Zahedi-Spung%2C%20a%20maternal%20fetal%20medicine%20specialist%20in%20Colorado%20and%20a%20fellow%20with%20Physicians%20for%20Reproductive%20Health%2C%20said%20when%20lethal%20fetal%20anomalies%20are%20diagnosed%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20only%20risk%20to%20that%20pregnant%20person%20and%20no%20benefit%20unfortunately%20for%20that%20innocent%20child.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20are%20putting%20your%20body%20through%20risks%20without%20any%20benefit%20because%20prolonging%20the%20pregnancy%20doesn't%20change%20the%20survival%20rate%2C%26quot%3B%20Zahedi-Spung%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20told%20Cox%20that%20her%20fetus%20has%20a%20condition%20known%20as%20trisomy%2018%2C%20which%20is%20when%20a%20baby%20has%20an%20extra%20copy%20of%20chromosome%2018.%20The%20diagnosis%20has%20a%20very%20high%20likelihood%20of%20miscarriage%20or%20stillbirth%2C%20and%20low%20survival%20rate.%20Doctors%20told%20Cox%20that%20inducing%20labor%20or%20carrying%20the%20baby%20to%20term%20could%20jeopardize%20her%20ability%20to%20have%20another%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrisomy%2018%20occurs%20in%20approximately%201%20in%202%2C500%20diagnosed%20pregnancies%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20College%20of%20Obstetricians%20and%20Gynecologists%20and%20the%20Society%20for%20Maternal-Fetal%20Medicine.%20There%20is%20no%20live%20birth%20in%20about%2070%25%20of%20pregnancies%20involving%20the%20diagnosis%20that%20proceed%20past%2012%20weeks%20gestational%20age%2C%20according%20to%20a%20legal%20filing%20that%20the%20two%20groups%20submitted%20to%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20termination%20of%20pregnancies%20because%20of%20fetal%20anomalies%20or%20other%20often-fatal%20medical%20problems%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fabortion-ending-pregnancies-over-grave-medical-problems-e504e595f5f4ea6139db3f7b5155ca85%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20seldom%20discussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20national%20debates%20over%20abortion.%20There%20are%20no%20recent%20statistics%20on%20the%20frequency%20of%20terminations%20for%20fetal%20anomalies%20in%20the%20US%20but%20experts%20say%20it's%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20total%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20long%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20strict%20abortion%20laws%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20even%20now%2C%20there%20are%20ongoing%20efforts%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fabortion-travel-ban-