0the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20there%20may%20be%20hundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%20of%20decisions%20that%20need%20to%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20President%20and%20Parliament%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20state%20government%20to%20ensure%20the%20day-to-day%20administration%20of%20the%20State%20continues%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20on%20the%20daily%20life%20of%20citizens%20is%20reduced.%20If%20every%20action%20taken%20by%20the%20President%20and%20Parliament%20on%20behalf%20of%20a%20State%20was%20open%20to%20challenge%2C%20this%20would%20effectively%20bring%20to%20the%20Court%20every%20person%20who%20disagreed%20with%20an%20action%20taken%20during%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20the%20Bench%20observed.%C2%A0%20Such%20an%20approach%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20the%20express%20text%20of%20Articles%20356%20(1)(a)%2C%20356%20(1)(b)%2C%20and%20356%20(1)(c)%20which%20entrusts%20the%20governance%20of%20the%20State%20with%20the%20Union%20Executive%20and%20Parliament%20during%20the%20period%20of%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20the%20Bench%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsupreme-court-article-370-verdict-injustice-writ-large%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Article%20370%20Judgment%20is%20Injustice%20Writ%20Large%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJudicial%20restraint%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20another%20reason%20why%20the%20level%20of%20judicial%20oversight%20over%20the%20actions%20taken%20during%20the%20imposition%20of%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20may%20not%20be%20as%20strict%20as%20suggested%20by%20the%20petitioners%2C%20the%20bench%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%20Most%20actions%20taken%20by%20the%20President%20for%20the%20interim%20governance%20of%20the%20State%20can%20be%20reversed%20by%20the%20State%20Government%20when%20it%20returns%20to%20power.%20Any%20orders%20passed%2C%20appointments%20ma