20not%20believe%20that%20the%20Court%20ought%20to%20sit%20in%20appeal%20over%20every%20decision%20taken%20by%20the%20President%20during%20the%20imposition%20of%20Article%20356%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Bench%20observed.%C2%A0%20One%20wonders%20whether%20the%20Bench%20abandoned%20judicial%20scrutiny%20on%20mere%20probabilities%20and%20hypotheses%2C%20and%20on%20sheer%20optimism%20of%20the%20political%20process%20correcting%20itself%20in%20the%20long%20run.%C2%A0%C2%A0%20One%20would%20assume%20that%20these%20are%20two%20distinct%20realms%2C%20and%20need%20not%20influence%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20Proclamation%20under%20Article%20356%20is%20in%20force%2C%20there%20are%20innumerable%20decisions%20which%20are%20taken%20by%20the%20Union%20Government%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20State%20Government%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20day-to-day%20administration%2C%20the%20Bench%20pointed%20out.%20Every%20decision%20and%20action%20taken%20by%20the%20Union%20Executive%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20State%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20challenge%2C%20it%20observed.%20Opening%20up%20a%20challenge%20to%20every%20decision%20would%20lead%20to%20chaos%20and%20uncertainty%2C%20it%20apprehended.%20It%20would%20in%20effect%20put%20the%20administration%20in%20the%20State%20at%20a%20standstill%2C%20it%20added.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CThis%20Court%20would%20enter%20into%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20valid%20exercise%20of%20power%20only%20when%20the%20petitioner%20makes%20a%20prima%20facie%20case%20that%20exercise%20of%20power%20is%20mala%20fide%20or%20extraneous.%20After%20the%20petitioner%20makes%20a%20prima%20facie%20case%2C%20the%20onus%20shifts%20to%20the%20Union%20to%20justify%20that%20the%20exercise%20of%20power%20had%20a%20reasonable%20nexus%20with%20the%20object%20of%20the%20Proclamation%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Bench%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChallenging%20the%20exercise%20of%20power%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20irreversibility%20would%20open%20the%20way%20for%20challenging%20every%20day%20administrative%20actions%2C%20the%20Bench%20elaborated.%20%E2%80%9CHence%2C%20we%20cannot%20accept%20the%20proposition%20which%20has%20been%20urged%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20petitioners%20that%20the%20exercise%20of%20power%20by%20the%20President%20under%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20Constitution%20can%20be%20challenged%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20it%20has%20given%20rise%20to%20irreversible%20consequences%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Bench%20added.%20Clearly%2C%20every%20irreversible%20consequence%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20challenge%2C%20but%20only%20those%20with%20potential%20impact%20on%20democracy%20and%20pluralism%2C%20which%20the%20Bench%20seems%20to%20have%20missed%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffour-important-takeaways-from-the-supreme-court-ruling-on-jammu-and-kashmir%5C%22%3EFour%20Important%20Takeaways%20From%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Ruling%20on%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESovereignty%20claim%20demolished%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20did%20not%20retain%20any%20element%20of%20sovereignty%20after%20the%20execution%20of%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20(IoA)%20and%20the%20issuance%20of%20the%20Proclamation%20dated%20November%2025%2C%201949%20by%20which%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20was%20adopted%2C%20the%20Bench%20ruled.%C2%A0%20The%20State%20did%20not%20have%20%E2%80%98internal%20sovereignty%E2%80%99%20which%20was%20distinguishable%20from%20the%20powers%20and%20privileges%20enjoyed%20by%20other%20States%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20Bench%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20reasoned%20that%20if%20the%20position%20that%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20sovereignty%20by%20virtue%20of%20Article%20370%20were%20to%20be%20accepted%2C%20it%20would%20follow%20that%20other%20States%20which%20had%20special%20arrangements%20with%20the%20Union%20also%20possessed%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20temporary%20provision%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20370%20has%20used%20the%20expression%20%E2%80%9Cexceptions%20and%20modifications%E2%80%9D%20at%20two%20distinct%20places%3A%20first%2C%20in%20sub-clause%20(d)%20of%20clause%20(1)%3B%20and%20second%20in%20clause%20(3).%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20the%20power%20to%20specify%20exceptions%20and%20modifications%20is%20entrusted%20to%20the%20President%3B%20in%20the%20case%20of%20sub-clause%20(d)%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20application%20of%20the%20other%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20State%20and%20in%20clause%20(3)%2C%20if%20the%20President%20orders%20that%20the%20provisions%20of%20Article%20370%20shall%20cease%20to%20be%20operative%2C%20the%20Bench%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20intrinsic%20reasons%20in%20Article%20370%20which%20support%20the%20view%20that%20the%20provision%20was%20not%20intended%20by%20the%20framers%20to%20be%20a%20permanent%20feature%20of%20the%20Constitution%20at%20the%20date%20of%20the%20adoption%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Part%20XXI%20of%20which%20Article%20370%20is%20a%20part%20specifies%20temporary%20and%20transitional%20provisions.%20In%20certain%20cases%2C%20the%20temporary%20provisions%20contained%20in%20Part%20XXI%20had%20a%20restriction%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20time%20over%20which%20they%20would%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20provisions%2C%20whether%20defined%20with%20reference%20to%20time%20or%20otherwise%20were%20temporary%20or%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20transitional%20in%20nature%2C%20the%20Bench%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20370%20was%20couched%20amidst%20other%20temporary%20and%20transitional%20provisions%20with%20a%20marginal%20note%20which%20indicates%20that%20its%20provisions%20were%20temporary.%20Article%20370%20was%20adopted%20at%20a%20point%20of%20time%20when%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20acceded%20to%20the%20Dominion%20of%20India%20by%20executing%20an%20IoA.%20Textually%2C%20Article%20370(1)(c)%20made%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20Article%201%20was%20to%20apply%20in%20its%20entirety%20to%20the%20State%20unlike%20other%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20application%20of%20which%20was%20to%20be%20governed%20by%20the%20requirement%20of%20consultation%20or%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20concurrence%2C%20the%20Bench%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20contention%20of%20the%20petitioners%20on%20the%20interpretation%20of%20Article%20370%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20is%20accepted%20then%20Article%20370(3)%20would%20become%20redundant%20and%20the%20provision%20would%20lose%20its%20temporary%20character.%20This%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20holding%20that%20Article%20370%20is%20a%20temporary%20provision%2C%20the%20Bench%20reasoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20President%20exercises%20the%20power%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20issuing%20a%20notification%20that%20Article%20370%20ceases%20to%20exist%2C%20the%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20would%20be%20fully%20constitutionally%20integrated%20with%20India%20similar%20to%20the%20other%20States%2C%20the%20Bench%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20power%20under%20Article%20370(1)%20and%20Article%20370(3)%20even%20when%20exercised%20to%20its%20fullest%20extent%20does%20not%20freeze%20the%20system%20of%20integration%20contemplated%20by%20Article%20370.%20It%20was%20intended%20to%20enhance%20constitutional%20integration%20between%20the%20Union%20and%20the%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Holding%20that%20the%20power%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20cannot%20be%20exercised%20after%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20would%20lead%20to%20freezing%20of%20the%20integration%20contrary%20to%20the%20purpose%20of%20introducing%20the%20provision%2C%20the%20Bench%20elaborated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20provision%20is%20temporary%20when%20the%20provision%20ceases%20to%20exist%20even%20without%20the%20exercise%20of%20the%20amending%20power%20either%20through%20the%20lapse%20of%20time%20or%20the%20absence%20of%20certain%20conditions.%20The%20provision%20could%20be%20temporary%20because%20of%20the%20time%20frame%2C%20that%20is%2C%20the%20provision%20states%20it%20would%20cease%20to%20have%20effect%20after%20the%20lapse%20of%20a%20particular%20time%20period%20or%20it%20could%20be%20temporary%20in%20view%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20specific%20circumstances.%20If%20Article%20370%20can%20only%20be%20repealed%20in%20the%20same%20manner%20as%20other%20provisions%20which%20are%20not%20placed%20within%20Part%20XXI%2C%20the%20distinction%20between%20temporary%20and%20other%20provisions%20is%20lost%2C%20the%20Bench%20further%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnion%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20contention%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20disagreed%20with%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20submission%20that%20the%20terms%20%E2%80%98Legislative%20Assembly%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Constituent%20Assembly%E2%80%99%20were%20used%20synonymously%20in%20the%20Constitution.%C2%A0%C2%A0%20The%20Union%20Government%20averred%20that%20the%20two%20organs%20were%20coequal%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20answered%20that%C2%A0%20Sub-clause%20(d)%20was%20inserted%20in%20recognition%20of%20the%20state%20of%20affairs%20which%20existed%20at%20the%20time%2C%20namely%2C%20that%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20had%20enacted%20certain%20laws%20for%20the%20State%20prior%20to%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly.%20This%20does%20not%20indicate%20that%20the%20two%20organs%20were%20at%20par%20with%20one%20another%2C%20the%20Bench%20pointed%20out.%20While%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20may%20have%20discharged%20the%20functions%20of%20the%20Legislature%20for%20some%20time%2C%20its%20role%20did%20not%20end%20there.%20The%20task%20of%20framing%20a%20Constitution%20is%20different%20from%20the%20function%20of%20enacting%20laws%2C%20the%20Bench%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%2C%20however%2C%20disagreed%20with%20petitioners%20who%20alleged%20non-application%20of%20mind%20by%20the%20Union%20Government.%C2%A0%20Non-application%20of%20mind%20cannot%20be%20claimed%20merely%20because%20the%20Constitution%20Order%20applies%20all%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%20one%20go%2C%20the%20Bench%20reasoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20did%20not%20cease%20to%20exist%20upon%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20When%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20dissolved%2C%20only%20the%20transitional%20power%20recognised%20in%20the%20proviso%20to%20Article%20370(3)%20which%20empowered%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20to%20make%20its%20recommendations%20ceased%20to%20exist.%20It%20did%20not%20affect%20the%20power%20held%20by%20the%20President%20under%20Article%20370(3)%2C%20the%20Bench%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20declared%20Paragraph%202%20of%20CO%20272%20by%20which%20Article%20370%20was%20amended%20through%20Article%20367%20as%20ultra%20vires%20Article%20370(1)(d)%20because%20it%20modifies%20Article%20370%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20without%20following%20the%20procedure%20prescribed%20to%20modify%20Article%20370.%20An%20interpretation%20clause%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20bypass%20the%20procedure%20laid%20down%20for%20amendment%2C%20the%20Bench%20reasoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CArticle%20370%20cannot%20be%20amended%20by%20exercise%20of%20power%20under%20Article%20370(1)(d).%20Recourse%20must%20have%20been%20taken%20to%20the%20procedure%20contemplated%20by%20Article%20370(3)%20if%20Article%20370%20is%20to%20cease%20to%20operate%20or%20is%20to%20be%20amended%20or%20modified%20in%20its%20application%20to%20the%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Bench%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Bench%20disagreed%20that%20the%20exercise%20of%20power%20by%20the%20President%20under%20Article%20370(1)(d)%20to%20issue%20CO%20272%20is%20mala%20fide.%20The%20President%2C%20in%20exercise%20of%20power%20under%20Article%20370(3)%2C%20can%20unilaterally%20issue%20a%20notification%20that%20Article%20370%20ceases%20to%20exist%2C%20the%20Bench%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President%20did%20not%20have%20to%20secure%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20State%20or%20Union%20Government%20acting%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20State%20Government%20under%20the%20second%20proviso%20to%20Article%20370(1)(d)%20while%20applying%20all%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20because%20such%20an%20exercise%20of%20power%20has%20the%20same%20effect%20as%20an%20exercise%20of%20power%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20for%20which%20the%20concurrence%20or%20collaboration%20with%20the%20State%20Government%20was%20not%20required%2C%20the%20Bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Bench%20held%20Paragraph%202%20of%20CO%20272%20issued%20by%20the%20President%20in%20exercise%20of%20power%20under%20Article%20370(1)(d)%20applying%20all%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20to%20the%20State%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20valid.%20Such%20an%20exercise%20of%20power%20is%20not%20mala%20fide%20merely%20because%20all%20the%20provisions%20were%20applied%20together%20without%20following%20a%20piece-meal%20approach%2C%20the%20Bench%20reasoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President%20had%20the%20power%20to%20issue%20a%20notification%20declaring%20that%20Article%20370(3)%20ceases%20to%20operate%20without%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20The%20continuous%20exercise%20of%20power%20under%20Article%20370(1)%20by%20the%20President%20indicates%20that%20the%20gradual%20process%20of%20constitutional%20integration%20was%20ongoing.%20The%20declaration%20issued%20by%20the%20President%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20is%20a%20culmination%20of%20the%20process%20of%20integration%20and%20as%20such%20is%20a%20valid%20exercise%20of%20power.%20Thus%2C%20CO%20273%20is%20valid%2C%20the%20Bench%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20made%20a%20virtue%20of%20its%20omission%20to%20examine%20the%20validity%20of%20downgrading%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20statehood%20to%20union%20territory%20by%20making%20it%20appear%20to%20be%20based%20on%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20promise%20that%20the%20Centre%20will%20consider%20restoring%20statehood.%20But%20the%20bench%20could%20as%20well%20have%20said%20as%20follows%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20only%20a%20means.%20Damn%20it!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702312900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11100850%2FUntitled-design-14-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fends-matter-not-the-means-decoding-scs-approval-for-reading-down-of-article-370%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20goal%20of%20making%20Article%20370%20inoperative%20was%20legitimate%20in%20itself%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20means%20adopted%20to%20achieve%20it%20cannot%20be%20elevated%20as%20a%20test%20to%20determine%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20goal%20itself%2C%20the%20judgment%20would%20seem%20to%20suggest.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fends-matter-not-the-means-decoding-scs-approval-for-reading-down-of-article-370%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mohan%20Yadav%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3A%20BJP's%20another%20surprise%20chief%20minister%20pick%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702312873000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-12%2F11%2Ffull%2F1702312854-5669.jpg%22%2C%22o